ng. He never pointed the weapon at me, but he made sure I knew it was there by taking it out if the small of his back and tucking it in the front waistband of his jeans for all to see. Charging at me he continues to yell and scream at me. My brother and sister heard and saw it all. They stood back and watched. I was frozen, I couldn‚Äôt move. All I could get out of my mouth to say was ‚Äúyour trespassed from here, leave‚Äù‚Ä¶.over and over again I asked him to leave. My sister even took cover behind the moving truck because she didn‚Äôt know what his intentions were. No one knew‚Ä¶.he snapped! I called the police immediately after and they advised me to talk to the Magistrate on duty. After the Police left my husband sent 2 threatening text messages and said he‚Äôs going to end it, it will be the last time I see my daughter etc. After grabbing a couple extra things, we went to the Magistrates office and I filed a criminal complaint. The magistrate issued 4 warrants for his arrest (Assault on a Female, Assault with a Deadly Weapon, Misd. Stalking, and Communicating Threat). We left the magistrates office and shortly after the Magistrate called me back and after reviewing my criminal complaint she thought it would be best if I applied for another Domestic Violence Protective Order. The following Monday, I went to Pender County Court house and applied. I was granted a temporary order for 10 days until our hearing. The hearing was again continued! I went to court on Wednesday March 25th 2009 in reference to my husbands criminal charges. It was taken to trial. I brought the two people that were with me that day, we brought the phone that contained the text messages he sent. I testified to what happened that day and the Assistant District Attorney presented the evidence. Mr. Friend didn‚Äôt deny anything. He admitted having the weapon, he admitted to sending the messages there was no denial in his testimony. His attorney made it clear that Mr. Friend was employed by Pender County Sheriffs Office previously (he was terminated at this point). We had a good case with solid evidence, with dates and times, with no time lapse between the incident, calling the police, and seeing the magistrate. Our evidence met every element for each crime that Mr. Friend admitted to. The charges were dismissed. The judge told me that I was using the Justice System to get back at Mr. Friend by taking out warrants. She also stated that if either one of us had any criminal charges pending that they better be dismissed! I was shocked, confused, upset at what had just occurred. The 50B hearing is on April 20th. I‚Äôm sure Pender County Courts will dismiss this as well despite of the solid testimonies and evidence that will be presented. I‚Äôm at a loss of words. When the threats start again and the harassment and the physical abuse, what am I supposed to do? Who can I turn to? I can‚Äôt call the police, I can‚Äôt go to the magistrate and take proper action to the crime that he has truthfully committed. I can‚Äôt turn to anyone for help and advice, because I‚Äôm immature and spiteful for applying for warrants and a DVPO with a legitimate reason and incident. I was so upset, I told the judge that I would be another N.C. statistic! No one will believe me (except the people who see it) and until I‚Äôm 6 feet under the ground, I will continue to live this dreadful life with no one there to turn to because I have exhausted my options in doing the right thing by going to MY justice system to expect some type of protection! I took great pride and confidence in choosing the profession that I have chosen. To help and protect citizens, to see justice being served. I‚Äôve advised many Domestic Violence women of their rights and I‚Äôve taken off my judgmental blinders to see these women‚Äôs point of view. I am at their level, I‚Äôm a victim of Domestic Violence, but yet Justice is blind and judgmental because we are both Police Officers. Do I not have the same rights citiz